node.text: Iceberg wedges with aubergine cream and super crunchy topping. The last in my outdoor series, and what a perfect sunny week for it! Iceberg makes a great base for building layers of flavour and texture. One of my favourite lettuces, contrary to popular opinion. Find the recipe in FLAVOUR or at my link in bio.

node.text: The last couple of months I’ve been following #LittleAmal’s extraordinary 8000km journey from the border of Syria to Manchester… A giant puppet of a 9year old refugee girl, inspiring support for refugees at events all along the route. Brilliant and beautiful to see. Sharing my favourite video from Chios here, but you can find much more @walkwithamal #TheWalk

node.text:
Two highlight from ROVI menu: 
Chard and braised pointed red cabbage with juniper and grapes. Stuffed with gorgozola, finished with reduced braising liquid, black pepper, purple basil and fresh thyme. Thank you, @neiljohncampbell 
And cobra beans from @ollofruit in Cornwall mixed with in-house tomato ferment, fried garlic and topped with @wolveslane_n22 basil. Slighty spicy, fresh.

node.text:
Face full of @hartsbakery pain au chocolat on way back to London. Thank you, Bristol!! Was short but very very sweet, just as expected. 
Especially huge thanks to @rootbristol and @robjhowell for an immortal meal last night: with a sensational kohlrabi with stem ginger, orange and spring onion and those beets with hazelnuts and blackberries. 😋 Oh, and almost forgot the buratta with courgette and dukkah. 
Loved sharing plates with @ellypear and @essexeating. I shall remember this time!!
And great  time on stage with @we_are_food for @penguinliveuk. 
Anna, you’re amazing!
